cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fixed points and introduces a sequent calculus. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses game semantics to model the solutions to recursive arena equations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the computation of solutions to recursive equations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper introduces winning functions and total winning strategies. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with formal language and syntax in the context of the introduced sequent calculus.
